column5: Had a great weekend on Simcoe again.Got out both days and got plenty of fish.Picked thrue the schools and got some great eaters.The shore was a liitle rough but once you past that it was smooth sailing right to our honey hole.Nobody was around us so it was nice and quiet.We had a couple of double headers which is always a riot!!Anyways time to put the ice gear away and get ready for open water!! Cheers!Time for the sportsman show,see you there!!
nice going I decided not to go on the weekend and now the whitefish are over till may......at lest I got the boat out of storage on the weekend
Awesome way to end the season DeerFisher Nice ones Thanks for sharing Leechman
Nice fish, especially in the crazy windy/rainy conditions this past weekend!
Yup, was a great close to another year of ice-fishing Simcoe.......Good friends,great weather and even fish to boot....TC and tight lines all....Chuck....
